summary: An FBI 302 report documenting a phone call on January 13, 2021, with an individual (name redacted) who expressed frustration about the return of her photographs provided to the FBI and her upset over identifying as a victim. She criticized another individual (name redacted) for not helping her or other girls and stated that person needed to take responsibility for her role with Jeffrey Epstein.

persons.name: Jeffrey Epstein
persons.context: The central figure in the investigation; the individual states another person needs to take responsibility for her role with him.

keyFacts: An individual contacted the FBI on January 13, 2021, seeking the return of photographs she had previously provided.
The individual expressed being upset about having to identify herself as a victim in the Epstein case.
The individual criticized another unnamed person for not helping her or other girls when she could have, and stated that person needed to take responsibility for her role with Jeffrey Epstein.
The document is an FBI 302 report, indicating it is a record of an interview or communication, and contains standard FBI disclaimers about its distribution.
